This paper is likely to belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it describes the implementation of a low-power precision-scalable processor for ConvNets. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as ConvNets are commonly used in image and video processing tasks. Additionally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the implementation of a neural network processor. It could also belong to cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it focuses on energy efficiency and dynamic precision-scalability, which are important considerations in embedded systems and control systems.
